&lt;p&gt;In the potassium binding protein Kbp, this domain is able to bind K  [[cite:PUB00101373]].&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This domain is also found in ArfA, a membrane protein required for supporting bacterial growth in acidic environments [[cite:PUB00101374]].&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This entry represents NAD- and NADP-binding domains with a core Rossmann-type fold, which consists of 3-layers α/β/α, where the six β-strands are parallel in the order 321456. Many different enzymes contain an NAD/NADP-binding domain, including:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;C-terminal domain of alcohol dehydrogenases [[cite:PUB00031657]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tyrosine-dependent oxidoreductases (also known as short-chain dehydrogenases) [[cite:PUB00000446]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;N-terminal domain of glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate dehydrogenase [[cite:PUB00023536]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NAD-binding domain of formate/glycerate dehydrogenases [[cite:PUB00032846]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;N-terminal domain of sirohaem synthase [[cite:PUB00029889]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;N-terminal domain of lactate dehydrogenase [[cite:PUB00025866]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;N-terminal domain of 6-phosphogluconate dehydrogenase (the β-sheet is extended to 8 strands) [[cite:PUB00041823]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;C-terminal domain of amino acid dehydrogenases (an extra N-terminal helix displaces the C-terminal helix [[cite:PUB00025375]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NAD-binding domain of certain potassium channels [[cite:PUB00025981]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;C-terminal domain of the transcriptional repressor Rex [[cite:PUB00032388]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ornithine cyclodeaminase [[cite:PUB00031693]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CoA-binding N-terminal domain of the alpha chain of succinyl-CoA synthetase [[cite:PUB00015984]]&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

